The paper proposes new algorithms for solving the symmetric tridiagonal eigenvalue problem, which is a numerical linear algebra problem. Therefore, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithms use divide-and-conquer techniques and hierarchical semiseparable (HSS) matrices, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and divide-and-conquer algorithms (cs.DC). The paper also includes experiments to show the efficiency of the algorithms, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or systems and control (cs.SY).
